      <heading level="2" numbered="true">Introduction</heading>
      <para>This document contains different examples of PSML markup for testing export functions.</para>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="11">
      <heading level="2" numbered="true">Inline formatting</heading>
      <para>
        <bold>Bold text</bold>
        is used to highlight important words or phrases, making them stand out for emphasis or easier scanning.
      </para>
      <para>
        <bold>Italic</bold>
        text is used to <italic>emphasize</italic> a word or phrase, indicate titles, or convey a different tone or
        meaning.
      </para>
      <para>
        <bold>Underline</bold>
        is used to <underline>draw attention to specific text</underline>, often for emphasis or to indicate links in
        digital content.
      </para>
      <para>
        <bold>Subscript</bold>
        is used to display characters slightly below the normal line of text, often in chemical formulas (e.g., H<sub>
        2</sub>O), while <bold>superscript</bold> raises characters above the line, commonly used for exponents or
        footnotes (e.g., x<sup>2</sup> or note<sup>2</sup>).
      </para>
      <para>
        <bold>Monospace</bold>
        or <bold>code</bold> text is used to display code, commands, or technical content with <monospace>uniform
        character spacing
      </monospace> for clarity and readability.
      </para>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="3">
      <heading level="2" numbered="true">Text blocks</heading>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="4">
      <heading level="3">Paragraphs</heading>
      <para>A paragraph is a distinct section of writing that focuses on a single idea or topic, helping to organize
        content and guide the reader through a coherent flow of thought. It typically begins with a topic sentence that
        introduces the main point, followed by supporting sentences that elaborate, explain, or provide evidence.
      </para>
      <para>Good paragraphs maintain unity, coherence, and appropriate transitions, making writing clearer and more
        readable. Whether in essays, reports, or articles, paragraphs structure information logically and allow the
        reader to process complex material in manageable segments.
      </para>
      <para indent="1" numbered="true">Focus on one main idea per paragraph.</para>
      <para indent="1" numbered="true">Use clear topic sentences to guide the reader.</para>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="5">
      <heading level="3">Blocks</heading>
      <block label="warning">
        <para>Be careful not to write too much – excessive detail can overwhelm readers and obscure your main point.
        </para>
      </block>
      <para>A longer block</para>
      <block label="tips">
        <para>Good writing style is clear, concise, and engaging, helping readers easily understand and stay interested
          in the content:
        </para>
        <list>
          <item>
            <para>Be direct</para>
          </item>
          <item>
            <para>Avoid jargon</para>
          </item>
          <item>
            <para>Use active voice</para>
          </item>
          <item>
            <para>Vary sentence length</para>
          </item>
          <item>
            <para>Edit ruthlessly</para>
          </item>
        </list>
      </block>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="8">
      <heading level="3">Lists</heading>
      <para>Here's a simple list of fruits:</para>
      <list>
        <item>Apple</item>
        <item>Banana</item>
        <item>Orange</item>
        <item>Mango</item>
      </list>
      <para>Here's a simple list of vegetables:</para>
      <nlist>
        <item>Carrot</item>
        <item>Broccoli</item>
        <item>Spinach</item>
        <item>Potato</item>
      </nlist>
    </fragment>
    <fragment id="10">
      <heading level="3">Preformatted</heading>
      <para>The following block contains JavaScript code:</para>
      <preformat role="lang-javascript">let name = "Alice";
let greeting = "Hello, " + name + "!";
console.log(greeting);
      </preformat>
      <para>The following has no role:</para>
      <preformat>Souvent, pour s’amuser, les hommes d’équipage
Prennent des albatros, vastes oiseaux des mers,
Qui suivent, indolents compagnons de voyage,
Le navire glissant sur les gouffres amers.
      </preformat>
    </fragment>
